meanings.definition: To produce more than (someone or something else)
meanings.sent1: The small bakery outproduced the big factory in making delicious cookies.
meanings.sent2: The new car model outproduced all its competitors in sales.
meanings.sent3: The tiny ant outproduced the lazy grasshopper in gathering food for winter.
meanings.sent4: The student outproduced the teacher in solving complex math problems.
meanings.sent5: The determined athlete outproduced all expectations in the race.

meanings.sent1: The local farm outproduced the supermarket in growing fresh vegetables.
meanings.sent2: The new technology outproduced the old methods in efficiency.
meanings.sent3: The ambitious squirrel outproduced the others in collecting nuts for winter.
meanings.sent4: The artist outproduced their previous work with a stunning masterpiece.
meanings.sent5: The factory outproduced its own record in manufacturing cars this month.
